name: src/classes/subscription.js
Subscription
description: Subscription is returned when you subscribe on stream.

name: src/operators/combineLatest.js
combineLatest
description:
Combines latest values of two or more streams, and returns new stream of an array filled with
these values. It will start emit latest values only when all streams has received at least one
value.

params.name: SubjectConstructor
params.description: Pass a constructor of result stream of an array with latest values

params.name: subjectList
params.description: An array of subjects/streams latest values of which needs to be collected

name: src/operators/debounce.js
debounce
description:
Debounce delays values emitted by the source stream, and drops previous
pending delayed emissions if a new value arrives on source stream.

params.name: SubjectConstructor
params.description: Pass a constructor of result/filtered stream

params.name: conditionStreamGenerator
params.description: a function that should return a stream, when new value arrives on that stream, debounced stream emits latest value from the source stream

name: src/operators/filter.js
filter
description: Filters one stream and returns another with only filtered values.

params.name: SubjectConstructor
params.description: Pass a constructor of result/filtered stream

params.name: conditionCallback
params.description: Predicate function, to test each element of the stream. Return true to keep the element, false otherwise

name: src/operators/merge.js
merge
description: Merges two or more streams into one.

params.name: SubjectConstructor
params.description: Pass a constructor of result/merged stream

params.name: subjectList
params.description: An array of subjects/streams to be merged

name: src/subjects/behaviourSubject.js
BehaviorSubject
description:
BehaviorSubject extends Subject. As Subject is a stream of values, BehaviorSubject
is also a stream, but a little bit different. The difference is that BehaviorSubject
remembers the last value that's been sent to it, and it sends this value to
new subscribers. Take a look at example.

name: src/subjects/replaySubject.js
ReplaySubject
description:
ReplaySubject extends Subject. As Subject is a stream of values, ReplaySubject
is also a stream, but a little bit different. The difference is that ReplaySubject
remembers all values that's been sent to it, and it sends all these values to
new subscribers. Take a look at example.

name: src/subjects/subject.js
Subject
description: Subject is a stream of values, that were pushed into it.
